{"author":{"id":"6bfbbb3a6a20bb933728de9f3bb4712ee3f7d01e5195c97bb8f2ab4068962e75"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1478185400,"nonce":"p1gGoO8Hx2xOZ1Hfo6Bt7lkS/Qk=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxODcwODUyOTU=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1020","origin":"github"},"title":"Prototype HIV NGS pipeline","message":"Following our discussion with @nekrut , I am creating an issue to outline essential components for creating a barebones HIV (or other short RNA virus) genomic analysis pipeline. \n\nKey steps for amplicon data (a very preliminary outline, many steps need to be fleshed out, initial focus is on wrapping some existing tools that we have worked with in the past)\n\n1. **Initial QC on NGS data**\n    - [x] Standard FASTQ filtering tools (q-score, read length, N's), e.g. [qfilt](https://github.com/veg/qfilt)\n    - [ ] paired end merging\n\n2. (If present in run) **random tag (PRIMER ID) processing**\n    - [ ] Binning and consensus construction \n    - [ ] Filtering using an error model, like the one from the [Swanstrom Lab](http://jvi.asm.org/content/89/16/8540)\n\n3. **Map to reference** (amplicon data), FASTQ =\u003e BAM\n     - [ ] Custom mappers (direct alignment, e.g. Smith Waterman) \n     - [x] [bealign] (https://github.com/veg/BioExt/)\n     - [ ] Standard short read mappers\n     - [ ] Coverage maps\n\n4. **Filter errors** (amplicon data). Need more options here\n    - [ ] [Model-based, multinomial, filtering](https://github.com/veg/HIV-NGS/tree/master/julia) Currently aligned FASTA =\u003e filtered aligned FASTA. Should be BAM =\u003e filtered BAM\n    - [ ] See if multiple alignments can be replaced with VCFs or something along these lines\n\n5. **Basic post processing** based on [TN93](https://github.com/veg/tn93)\n   - [ ] Generate consensus sequences\n   - [ ] Sliding window haplotypes (simple read merging, large overlap)\n   - [ ] Report amino-acid frequencies by position (and DRAMs) -- need to write\n\n6. **Basic phylogenetics** (need to pull out some code from https://github.com/veg/HIV-NGS)\n\n6. **HIV clustering**\n   - [ ] hivnetworkcsv \n\n\nA few references to existing (published) pipelines\n\n0. [The VEG group pipeline](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/27774305)\n1. [Sanger WGS](http://biorxiv.org/content/early/2015/12/24/035154)\n2. [ShoRAH](https://github.com/ozagordi/shorah)\n3. [Richard Neher's intrahost analysis app](http://hiv.tuebingen.mpg.de/method/)\n4. [An older comparative study of haplotype reconstruction](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3789152/)\n\nWRAP DATAMONKEY INTO GALAXY","files":null}]}